{"id":4258,"date":"2024-03-06T11:59:57","date_gmt":"2024-03-06T11:59:57","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/?p=4258"},"modified":"2024-03-06T11:59:57","modified_gmt":"2024-03-06T11:59:57","slug":"mern-stack-vs-python","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.skillvertex.com\/blog\/mern-stack-vs-python\/","title":{"rendered":"Mern Stack Vs Python"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<div class=\"wp-block-rank-math-toc-block\" id=\"rank-math-toc\" id=\"rank-math-toc\"><p>Table of Contents<\/p><nav><ul><li ><a href=\"#mern-stack-vs-python\">Mern Stack Vs Python<\/a><\/li><li ><a href=\"#faq-mern-stack-vs-python\">FAQ- Mern Stack Vs Python<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"mern-stack-vs-python\">Mern Stack Vs Python<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Choosing between Python and the MERN stack is like deciding between different tools. The decision to choose between Mern stack and Python often relies on the team&#8217;s preference and experience, rather than following what&#8217;s popular or focusing solely on performance. Sometimes, the project&#8217;s requirements dictate the tools you use for your part of the solution.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The main goal is to create a technical solution or tool to solve a problem. Most widely used languages and frameworks can help you achieve that goal. It&#8217;s essential not to get stuck on picking a particular language or framework. If you&#8217;re new to coding, choose one and stick with it. Front-end development typically involves JS\/HTML\/CSS, while data science may focus more on Python, R, Julia, and so on.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Python is a versatile programming language known for its straightforward syntax and is commonly used for various tasks. However, it&#8217;s not typically used for front-end development. If you&#8217;re working on the backend, you can use Python with frameworks like Flask or Django. However, if you&#8217;re learning JavaScript, it&#8217;s practical to use JavaScript for both the front-end and backend.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>MERN stands for Mongo, Express, React, and Node. In this stack, MongoDB serves as the database backend, Express is a module for server applications in Node.js, React is a UI library, and Node.js is the runtime that powers everything, using JavaScript.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"faq-mern-stack-vs-python\">FAQ- Mern Stack Vs Python<\/h2>\n\n\n<div id=\"rank-math-faq\" class=\"rank-math-block\">\n<div class=\"rank-math-list \">\n<div id=\"faq-question-1702290682283\" class=\"rank-math-list-item\">\n<h4 class=\"rank-math-question \">Q1. Is Python better than full stack?<\/h4>\n<div class=\"rank-math-answer \">\n\n<p>Ans. Deciding between Java and Python for full-stack development relies on the specific project needs. Java is preferred for high performance and scalability, while Python is chosen for rapid development and ease of use.<\/p>\n\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"faq-question-1702290689728\" class=\"rank-math-list-item\">\n<h4 class=\"rank-math-question \">Q2. Is Python full stack in demand?<\/h4>\n<div class=\"rank-math-answer \">\n\n<p>Ans. Python Full Stack Developers are highly sought after in diverse industries. Companies, whether startups or established enterprises, are in need of their expertise to create and manage web applications. Possessing the right skills and experience opens up a broad spectrum of job opportunities in the field.<\/p>\n\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div id=\"faq-question-1702290704268\" class=\"rank-math-list-item\">\n<h4 class=\"rank-math-question \">Q3. What is the salary of MERN stack developer vs Python developer?<\/h4>\n<div class=\"rank-math-answer \">\n\n<p>Ans. The average salary for a Full Stack Python Developer is INR 4.3 lakhs, while a Full Stack JavaScript Developer earns an average of INR 7.68 lakhs. For MERN Stack Developers, the average salary is INR 4.2 lakhs.<\/p>\n\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Mern Stack Vs 